# Raspberry Pi 4 ↔ ESP32 UART Communication Using Linux Inbuilt UART Driver

## Project Overview

This project demonstrates **UART (Universal Asynchronous Receiver Transmitter) communication** between a **Raspberry Pi 4 Model B** running **Embedded Linux (Debian Bookworm)** and an **ESP32** using the **Linux inbuilt UART driver (PL011 / Mini UART)**.

The objective is to understand the Linux serial communication stack, configure UART on Raspberry Pi, and implement reliable full-duplex communication with an ESP32.

---

# Objectives

* Understand Linux UART architecture.
* Configure UART on Raspberry Pi.
* Learn the Linux TTY subsystem.
* Perform UART communication using POSIX APIs.
* Interface Raspberry Pi with ESP32.
* Implement UART transmit and receive.
* Build a reusable UART communication library.
* Understand UART debugging techniques.

---

