# Project Architecture

```text
                 Raspberry Pi 4
          --------------------------
          User Application (C)
                  |
            POSIX APIs
                  |
          Linux TTY Subsystem
                  |
         PL011 / Mini UART Driver
                  |
            UART Hardware
                  |
      TX -------------------- RX
      RX -------------------- TX
      GND ------------------ GND
                  |
                ESP32
           HardwareSerial
```

---

# UART Communication Flow

```text
Application

↓

write()

↓

POSIX API

↓

TTY Subsystem

↓

UART Driver

↓

UART Registers

↓

GPIO Pins

↓

ESP32 UART

↓

Serial Monitor
```

---

# UART Pin Connections

| Raspberry Pi | ESP32        |
| ------------ | ------------ |
| GPIO14 (TX)  | GPIO16 (RX2) |
| GPIO15 (RX)  | GPIO17 (TX2) |
| GND          | GND          |

---

# Raspberry Pi UART Configuration

Enable UART using:

```bash
sudo raspi-config
```

Navigate:

```
Interface Options
    ↓
Serial Port
```

Configure:

```
Login Shell over Serial : No

Serial Hardware : Yes
```

Reboot:

```bash
sudo reboot
```

Verify:

```bash
ls -l /dev/serial0

readlink -f /dev/serial0

dmesg | grep tty
```

