---

# Important POSIX APIs

| Function    | Description                 |
| ----------- | --------------------------- |
| open()      | Open UART device            |
| close()     | Close UART device           |
| read()      | Receive data                |
| write()     | Transmit data               |
| tcgetattr() | Get UART configuration      |
| tcsetattr() | Configure UART              |
| select()    | Monitor UART events         |
| poll()      | Event polling               |
| fcntl()     | Configure non-blocking mode |
| ioctl()     | Device control              |

---

# UART Debugging Commands

Check UART devices:

```bash
ls /dev/tty*
```

Check serial mapping:

```bash
ls -l /dev/serial0
```

Find actual UART:

```bash
readlink -f /dev/serial0
```

Configure UART:

```bash
stty -F /dev/serial0 115200
```

Display UART configuration:

```bash
stty -F /dev/serial0 -a
```

Monitor UART:

```bash
minicom -D /dev/serial0 -b 115200
```

Kernel messages:

```bash
dmesg | grep tty
```

